author: Deanese Williams-Harris
title: Police look to identify woman found on North Side - Chicago Tribune
text:
Police are asking for the public's help identifying a woman who was found on the North Side in the Lakeview neighborhood.
The woman, who police believe is 40 to 60 years of age, was found in the area of Belmont Avenue and Broadway. She was wearing a cream-colored hat, black coat, cream-colored sweater and brown suede boots, police said.
She's white with a light complexion and gray hair. She's about 5 feet 7 inches tall and weighs about 150 to 160 pounds, police said.
Anyone with information should contact the Area North Special Victims Unit at 312-744-8266.
